description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and North Korean leader Kim Jong Un signed a strategic partnership during an elaborately choreographed state visit, deepening ties when there's growing U.S. concern about North Korea's help for the Russian war effort in Ukraine. NBC News' Janis Mackey Frayer reports.
title: Putin and Kim Jong Un sign strategic partnership, deepening ties

description: Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu accused the U.S. of withholding weapons and ammunition from Israel, but the White House said it had no idea what Netanyahu was talking about. In response, the White House postponed a meeting with Israeli officials. NBC News' Kelly O'Donnell reports.
title: Netanyahu accuses U.S. of withholding military aid for Israel

description: Two activists from the Just Stop Oil group were arrested after spraying orange paint on part of the 4,500-year-old stone structure, Stonehenge. The incident came just a day before thousands of people are expected to gather there to celebrate the summer solstice.
title: Watch: Climate protesters spray paint on Stonehenge

description: A bipartisan congressional delegation met with the Dalai Lama at his residence in India's Dharamshala, sparking anger from China which views the exiled spiritual leader of Tibetan Buddhism as a separatist.
title: Congressional delegation meets with the Dalai Lama, sparking anger in Beijing

description: Gordon Black, a 34-year-old U.S. staff sergeant who was detained in May in Russia's Vladivostok, was found guilty on charges of theft and threats to kill his girlfriend and sentenced to three years and nine months in a Russian penal colony. Black had pleaded not guilty to charges of threatening to kill his girlfriend, but admitted he was "partially" guilty of stealing from her.
title: U.S. soldier sentenced to nearly 4 years in Russian prison colony
